  <section>
    <h2>Why Online Gaming Requires Special Attention</h2>
    <p>
      Online gaming is no longer a solitary activity - it's a social ecosystem where millions of players interact in
      real-time. While gaming can build problem-solving skills and friendships, it also creates risks: exposure to
      strangers, inappropriate language, predatory behavior, cyberbullying, addictive mechanics, and unexpected costs.
      Unlike social media where parents might see posts, gaming conversations happen in voice chat and disappear, making
      supervision more challenging.
    </p>

    <div class="alert alert-info">
      <strong>Key Fact:</strong> 75% of children ages 9-12 play online games. 41% of online gamers have experienced harassment
      while playing. Understanding the risks is essential for modern parenting.
    </div>
  </section>

